docs.lead_paragraph: At a time early yesterday morning when the lights went out in the front rooms and in the dingy back rooms of drinking dives, young men whose appearance marked them as gangsters sauntered with exaggerated indolence out of range of the arc lamps of Eighth and Ninth Avenues into the shadows of the side streets, between Thirty-seventh and Forty-second.

headline.main: DETECTIVE'S SHOT KILLS A GANGSTER; Two Others Wounded, One Mortally, in an Early Morning Gang Conflict.

docs.abstract: East Side contest held, prizes awarded
